cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.DC 

The paper discusses an information retrieval architecture that operates along the lines of human ways of searching, which is a core topic in the field of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The architecture is decentralized and agent-oriented, which aligns with the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and System and Control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of spatiotemporal references as a primary information criterion, which relates to the sub-categories of Spatial Databases (cs.SD) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
